AN ACT relating to charter schools; revising provisions governing the membership
of the State Public Charter School Authority; revising provisions
establishing the local educational agency that is responsible for
performing certain functions with respect to charter schools; clarifying
requirements for certain information to be included in an application to
renew the charter contract of a charter school; and providing other
matters properly relating thereto.
Legislative Counsel’s Digest:
1 Existing law creates the State Public Charter School Authority for the purpose of, among
2 other duties: (1) sponsoring charter schools; and (2) providing oversight to the charter schools
3 it sponsors. (NRS 388A.150) Existing law further establishes that the Authority consists of
4 nine members, the manner of appointing those members and the qualifications of those
5 members. (NRS 388A.153) Section 1 of this bill provides that the nine members appointed
6 under existing law are the voting members of the Authority and that the voting members must
7 be at least 21 years of age. Section 1 also establishes the requirements governing the members
8 of the Authority that apply to all members, including voting and nonvoting members, and the
9 requirements that apply only to voting members. Section 2 of this bill makes a conforming
10 change to clarify that only voting members of the Authority are required to complete certain
11 training required by existing law. (NRS 388A.155) Section 3 of this bill makes a conforming
12 change to clarify that a majority of the voting members, rather than all members: (1) is
13 authorized to call a meeting of the Authority; and (2) constitutes a quorum to enable the
14 Authority to exercise its power and authority. (NRS 388A.156)
15 Under existing law, the number of members of the Authority who may be teachers or
16 administrators employed by a charter school or charter management organization in this State
17 is limited to two members. (NRS 388A.153) Section 1 revises the qualifications for a teacher
18 or administrator employed by a charter school or charter management organization to be
19 eligible to serve as a member of the Authority by: (1) removing the requirement that the
20 charter school or charter management organization employing the teacher or administrator

